<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1595,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,276,1827,1853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">Notes.</emphasis>
Although a male is explicitely mentioned in the original description, there is no indication that only one specimen was examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernhauer" box="[599,813,1866,1892]" pageId="1" pageNumber="41" refString="Bernhauer, M. (1912) Zur Staphylinidenfauna von Sudamerika (10. Beitrag). Verhandlungen der k. k. zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 62, 26 - 48." type="journal article" year="1912">
Bernhauer (
<number box="[739,804,1866,1892]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. All the three specimens listed above agree with the original description and considered to have been 
<typeStatus box="[726,828,1905,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">syntypes</typeStatus>
prior to the present 
<typeStatus box="[1065,1172,1905,1931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation.
